<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,882,1012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,243,882,904]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[376,532,882,904]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="glaucotinctus">
<emphasis box="[376,532,882,904]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">P. glaucotinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differing in the nrITS sequence (
<accessionNumber box="[915,1028,882,904]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/HM562132" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">HM562132</accessionNumber>
) and in having predominantly subglobose basidiospores (Qm = 1.15) and longer cheilocystidia (up to 94 µm long).
</paragraph>
